texto: Machine learning (ML) is a field of study in artificial intelligence concerned with the development and study of statistical algorithms that can learn from data and generalize to unseen data, and thus perform tasks without explicit instructions.Within a subdiscipline in machine learning, advances in the field of deep learning have allowed neural networks, a class of statistical algorithms, to surpass many previous machine learning approaches in performance.

Machine Learning. Data Mining: Definition, Benefits, and Common Techniques. Finding hidden insights in unmanaged data has been challenging for businesses for decades. Businesses have been seeking efficient data access and effective processing techniques to help them deal with vast amounts of data. That’s where data science and data mining techniques emerge. Here is a detailed guide about understanding data mining, its benefits, types, steps, best practices, its future, its limitations, and the difference between it and AI.

Real Madrid is the only team in the history of European football that holds 10 UEFA titles. The Spanish giants clinch their first UEFA Cup Winner's Cup in 1999. The triumph came after they beat Scottish side, Glasgow Rangers. The following year, Real Madrid won their first UEFA Supercup and also claimed the LaLiga trophy. The Madrid team played some scintillating football and dominated teams in Spain. The following year, the Los Blancos went on to claim yet another league title and reached their first UEFA Champions League Final.

Machine Learning is the artificial intelligence that provides systems the ability to automatically learn and improve from experience without being explicitly programmed. By combining large datasets, statistical modeling and computational power, machine learning delivers advanced capabilities, such as pattern recognition, classification and regression. With Machine Learning, your system can: 1. Learn from your data 2. Identify patterns in data 3. Make predictions

Machine Learning is the technology that enables the computer systems to learn from the data and make decisions with minimal human intervention. It is a sub-field of Artificial Intelligence (AI) that uses statistical techniques to give computers the ability to learn with data, without being explicitly programmed.  It’s getting so much attention these days, mainly because of the surge in data, and how organizations are looking to capitalize on this data to make their businesses more efficient and profitable.

Real Madrid is considering bringing back former coach Zinedine Zidane to replace Julen Lopetegui after only five LaLiga matches into the season, the Spanish sports daily AS reported Sunday. Zidane has been out of management since leaving Real Madrid in May after winning three successive Champions League titles. The French coach has been linked with various jobs since he left, including Tottenham Hotspur, who recently appointed Barcelona boss Ernesto Valverde as manager. But AS claimed on Sunday that Real director-general Jose Angel Sanchez had held talks with former player Zidane in recent weeks about a potential return to the Santiago Bernabeu.
